The paper proposes a novel approach for one-class classification using a convolutional neural network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of cross-entropy loss and pre-trained CNNs, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on datasets related to abnormality detection and novelty detection, which are common problems in computer security and cryptography, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses images as input data, which is a common format in multimedia processing, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
